question_en:
Will the Minister of AYUSH be pleased to state:
(a) whether there is an acute shortage of trained AYUSH doctors and pharmacists across the
country, if so, the details thereof;
(b) the number of vacant positions in Government hospitals and health centres;
(c) whether the Government has delayed recruitment under the National AYUSH Mission;
and
(d) if so, the details thereof?

Will the Minister of EDUCATION be pleased to state:
(a) whether schools and other educational institutions run by the Government teach students in their
mother tongue, except Hindi or a significant language;
(b) if so, whether the Government has any language policy governing the medium of instruction in
educational institutions;
(c) if not, the details of the medium of language presently adopted in such institutions;
(d) the number of students who have benefited from the Government's schemes and enrolled for Post-
Graduate (PG) from 2014 till date; and
(e) the details of recruitment of teaching faculty for education institutions run by the Government, social
category-wise, language-wise and State-wise?

Will the Minister of EDUCATION be pleased to state:
(a) whether it is a fact that the post of Associate Professors in Central Universities/State
Universities/Higher Education Institutions receiving grant-in-aid are lying vacant at present in
various categories (General, Scheduled Castes, Scheduled Tribes, Other Backward Classes and
Economically Weaker Sections) in the country;
(b) if so, the details thereof along with the total number of posts lying vacant, category-wise
and institution-wise;
(c) the steps taken so far by the Government to fill these vacant positions;
(d) whether any specific timeline has been set for filling-up these posts; and
(e) if so, the details thereof and if not, the reasons therefor?

Will the Minister of Women and Child Development be pleased to state:
(a) whether the implementation of schemes related to women and child development is
progressing at a slow pace in Bhagalpur district of Bihar;
(b) if so, the details thereof;
(c) the number of Anganwadi Centres currently functional along with the number of such
Centres proposed in the said district;
(d) the number of women and children who have been benefited under the POSHAN
Abhiyaan and the Pradhan Mantri Matru Vandana Yojana in the said district till date;
and
(e) the details of the steps taken by the Government in the said district to promote women's
empowerment, ensure their safety and improve nutritional outcomes in the said district?
